{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀμαθ-ής</b>, ές, <br /> (μαθεῖν) <b>ignorant, stupid,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.33, 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 169, etc.; ἔθνεα ἀμαθέστατα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.46; ἀνὴρ πένης, εἰ καὶ γένοιτο μὴ ἀ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 421, +others, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 135; ἀ. καὶ βδελυρός [prev. author] “Eq.” 193; ἀμαθεστάτους πάντων ἀνθρώπων 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.2; ἀ. τὴν [ἐκείνων] ἀμαθίαν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 22e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to δεξιός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.82 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of animals, such as wild boars, <b>unmanageable,</b> θυμώδη καὶ ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 488b14\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>without knowledge of</b> a thing, <b>unlearned in</b> it, -έστερος τοῦ καλοῦ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 417; λῃστείας 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.41, compare 3.37; ἀ. περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Eryxias” 394e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “La.” 194d; πρός τι “Lg.” 679d. \">Refs</a>]<i>adverb</i> -θῶς <b>ignorantly, through ignorance,</b> ἥμαρτον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 874: _comparative_ -έστερον, τῶν νόμων ὑπεροψίας παιδεύεσθαι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] to be educated <b>with too little learning</b> to despise the laws, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.84; -έστερόν πως εἰπὲ καὶ σαφέστερον \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>less learnedly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1445. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> of moral defects, <b>unfeeling, inhuman,</b>